This paper deals with secure multiparty computation, cryptocurrency, and stateful contracts, which are all topics that fall under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the efficiency of the protocols, which suggests that it may fall under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper specifically focuses on the game of poker, which is a topic that falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the formalization of the stateful contract model, which suggests that it may fall under the category of software engineering (cs.SC) or cryptography and security (cs.CY).
